<storykicker><![CDATA[Italian supercar manufacturer Ferrari is working on a convertible version of its most powerful supercar ever, the LaFerrari.<br />]]></storykicker>
<storybody><![CDATA[<p>Ferrari is working on its most powerful open-top car till date, the LaFerrari Spider. Based on its most powerful car ever the LaFerrari, the convertible version of the car will also have a limited production run of 150 cars only.The news was revealed by Gordon Ramsay on the rebooted Top Gear Show and has also been confirmed by Sergio Marchionne, the CEO of Ferrari.</p><p>The LaFerrari Spider will be powered by the same 6.3-liter V-12 engine that was present on the LaFerrari. It will also gets the KERS power system that was present on its sibling and is also used in F1. The total power output of the system is 950 bhp and 900 Nm of peak torque. The electric motor supplies 160 of those ponies. The power is sent to the rear wheels via a seven-speed dual clutch transmission.</p><p><a target="_blank" href="http://indiatoday.intoday.in/auto/story/ferrari-gtc4lusso-debuts-at-geneva-motor-show/1/610326.html" mce_href="http://indiatoday.intoday.in/auto/story/ferrari-gtc4lusso-debuts-at-geneva-motor-show/1/610326.html">Also Read: 

 
Ferrari GTC4Lusso debuts at Geneva Motor Show</a> </p><p>Potential customers have already been approached by Ferrari, with all of them chosen by the Italian manufacturer. It just might be the case that all the models of the LaFerrari get sold before the world even gets a glimpse of the car.</p><p>Ferrari had often hinted in the past about a convertible version of Enzo's successor, but nothing had been etched in stone until now.</p>]]></storybody>
